1
00:00:01,708 --> 00:00:04,625
<i>[light music]</i>

2
00:00:04,708 --> 00:00:11,250
<i>♪ ♪</i>

3
00:00:11,333 --> 00:00:14,792
[thumping]

4
00:00:14,875 --> 00:00:21,833
<i>♪ ♪</i>

5
00:00:51,833 --> 00:00:58,792
<i>♪ ♪</i>

6
00:01:18,667 --> 00:01:22,750
- Marcela, what are you doing?

7
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:24,750
Come on.
I know you're in there.

8
00:01:27,750 --> 00:01:29,333
Marcela!

9
00:01:29,417 --> 00:01:30,833
[speaking Spanish]

10
00:01:30,917 --> 00:01:33,875
<i>[lively music]</i>

11
00:01:33,958 --> 00:01:38,042
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12
00:01:40,208 --> 00:01:41,750
Are you kidding me?

13
00:01:41,833 --> 00:01:42,708
- Where have you been?

14
00:01:42,792 --> 00:01:44,833
I was waiting for you
at school.

15
00:01:44,917 --> 00:01:47,375
- I was at the library,
Marcela.

16
00:01:47,458 --> 00:01:49,000
Expanding our knowledge.

17
00:01:49,083 --> 00:01:50,792
Something you wouldn't
know about.

18
00:01:53,417 --> 00:01:54,792
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19
00:01:54,875 --> 00:01:58,125
[clattering]

20
00:01:58,208 --> 00:01:59,208
All right.
What did you take?

21
00:01:59,292 --> 00:02:00,708
- I didn't take anything.

22
00:02:00,792 --> 00:02:01,958
- Oh, come on, Marcela,

23
00:02:02,042 --> 00:02:04,042
you're acting weird
and locked the door?

24
00:02:04,125 --> 00:02:06,083
- I was getting changed.

25
00:02:06,167 --> 00:02:09,042
You wanted to walk in
on me changing?

26
00:02:09,125 --> 00:02:10,500
Gross.

27
00:02:11,833 --> 00:02:14,083
- Then why are you
still in uniform, then?

28
00:02:14,167 --> 00:02:15,292
- Why are you home so late?

29
00:02:15,375 --> 00:02:16,292
- Don't change the subject.

30
00:02:16,375 --> 00:02:18,542
Why were you going
through my stuff again?

31
00:02:18,625 --> 00:02:21,000
- You're lucky Mom's working
till 10:00 tonight.

32
00:02:21,083 --> 00:02:23,792
Gives you time
to "study" some more.

33
00:02:23,875 --> 00:02:25,708
- [chuckles]
Maybe I will.

34
00:02:25,792 --> 00:02:28,875
But did you notice
Mom left a note on the fridge?

35
00:02:28,958 --> 00:02:31,917
I think it said she'll be home
at 5:00 p.m.

36
00:02:35,083 --> 00:02:36,583
Psych!
What do we have here?

37
00:02:36,667 --> 00:02:37,875
Stealing yet again?

38
00:02:37,958 --> 00:02:40,333
- Give that back!
[grunts]

39
00:02:40,417 --> 00:02:42,125
- I should just do this
until Mom comes home.

40
00:02:42,208 --> 00:02:43,667
- [grunts]

41
00:02:45,417 --> 00:02:46,833
What do we have here?

42
00:02:46,917 --> 00:02:49,917
<i>[lively music]</i>

43
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,792
- Marcela!

44
00:02:51,875 --> 00:02:53,708
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45
00:02:53,792 --> 00:02:54,917
[dialing rotary phone]

46
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:56,083
- You wouldn't.

47
00:02:56,167 --> 00:02:58,250
<i>[phone line trilling]</i>

48
00:02:58,333 --> 00:02:59,250
Okay, fine.
Here.

49
00:02:59,333 --> 00:03:00,542
Let's hand off
at the same time.

50
00:03:00,625 --> 00:03:02,042
<i>[line trilling]</i>

51
00:03:02,125 --> 00:03:03,667
- On three?

52
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:06,625
<i>[percussive music]</i>

53
00:03:06,708 --> 00:03:08,375
<i>♪ ♪</i>

54
00:03:08,458 --> 00:03:09,750
One...

55
00:03:09,833 --> 00:03:12,417
<i>♪ ♪</i>

56
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:13,417
Two...

57
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:15,542
<i>♪ ♪</i>

58
00:03:15,625 --> 00:03:18,875
[gasps] No!
- Oops.

59
00:03:18,958 --> 00:03:20,708
What is that?
- It's n-nothing.

60
00:03:20,792 --> 00:03:22,542
Just something I found.

61
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,750
<i>♪ ♪</i>

62
00:03:26,833 --> 00:03:29,958
Don't tell Mama.

63
00:03:30,042 --> 00:03:31,333
- Did you get this
from Mom's room?

64
00:03:31,417 --> 00:03:33,208
[scoffs] Oh, great.
You opened it too.

65
00:03:33,292 --> 00:03:35,542
- No, it was like that
when I found it.

66
00:03:35,625 --> 00:03:37,333
- When did this come in?

67
00:03:37,417 --> 00:03:38,417
- It's new.

68
00:03:40,375 --> 00:03:41,333
Go ahead.

69
00:03:41,417 --> 00:03:43,625
Check what it says.
I have a feeling it may be--

70
00:03:43,708 --> 00:03:44,917
- No.

71
00:03:46,042 --> 00:03:47,167
- But Rogelio,
this may be our chance to--

72
00:03:47,250 --> 00:03:48,250
- Shh.

73
00:03:49,583 --> 00:03:50,750
- I really think
that this will--

74
00:03:50,833 --> 00:03:52,042
- Shh.

75
00:03:52,125 --> 00:03:53,917
- Be from--
- Shh.

76
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:54,917
- Papa!

77
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,917
- Marcela,
if Mom hid this from us,

78
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,375
then it was for a good reason.

79
00:03:58,458 --> 00:04:00,750
This is way beyond
your mental capacity.

80
00:04:00,833 --> 00:04:02,083
I'm gonna hold onto this.

81
00:04:03,417 --> 00:04:05,000
Or maybe I should just
give this to Mom instead.

82
00:04:05,083 --> 00:04:07,542
- Rogelio...
- Leave this to us adults.

83
00:04:09,125 --> 00:04:12,542
<i>[mischievous music]</i>

84
00:04:12,625 --> 00:04:14,875
<i>♪ ♪</i>

85
00:04:17,125 --> 00:04:18,667
- Come on.
I gotta show you something.

86
00:04:18,750 --> 00:04:20,125
- Look, I don't have time
for this, okay?

87
00:04:20,208 --> 00:04:21,167
I gotta go to--

88
00:04:21,250 --> 00:04:23,875
- To the library
and study with your friends?

89
00:04:23,958 --> 00:04:27,083
Or should I say Selena?

90
00:04:27,167 --> 00:04:28,542
[imitating smooching]

91
00:04:28,625 --> 00:04:30,792
Don't worry, I'll let Mom know.

92
00:04:30,875 --> 00:04:33,125
- Okay, look.
Just make it quick, okay?

93
00:04:33,208 --> 00:04:34,333
Snitch.

94
00:04:34,417 --> 00:04:37,542
- Okay, what I'm about
to show you is top secret.

95
00:04:37,625 --> 00:04:39,500
No one can know about this,

96
00:04:39,583 --> 00:04:41,333
especially Mama.

97
00:04:41,417 --> 00:04:42,958
Do you promise to keep this
locked in your heart

98
00:04:43,042 --> 00:04:44,583
till death do you part?

99
00:04:44,667 --> 00:04:45,583
- Yeah, sure.

100
00:04:45,667 --> 00:04:47,083
- Cross your heart.

101
00:04:49,083 --> 00:04:50,958
<i>♪ ♪</i>

102
00:04:51,042 --> 00:04:52,333
Okay.

103
00:04:52,417 --> 00:04:54,208
So I've been doing
some research,

104
00:04:54,292 --> 00:04:56,250
and I think I may know
a bit more about Papa

105
00:04:56,333 --> 00:04:59,000
than you, Rogelio.

106
00:04:59,083 --> 00:05:01,542
Remember Papa's first letter
last summer?

107
00:05:01,625 --> 00:05:03,958
He never really mentioned
who he was working for,

108
00:05:04,042 --> 00:05:06,208
but sent us these gifts
from San Diego.

109
00:05:06,292 --> 00:05:08,583
He sent me this penny
with a boot on it.

110
00:05:08,667 --> 00:05:11,375
And you got a deck of cards
with cheerleaders on them.

111
00:05:11,458 --> 00:05:13,958
- Wait, how did you--
- I found it under your bed.

112
00:05:15,875 --> 00:05:18,708
So I decided to keep it
in the name of research.

113
00:05:18,792 --> 00:05:21,833
<i>Anyway, Papa's job,</i>
<i>according to him,</i>

114
00:05:21,917 --> 00:05:23,667
<i>was in Los Angeles.</i>

115
00:05:23,750 --> 00:05:25,292
The only place that has these

116
00:05:25,375 --> 00:05:28,208
has to be a place
known for cowboys.

117
00:05:28,292 --> 00:05:31,667
The cheerleaders on your cards
aren't just any cheerleaders,

118
00:05:31,750 --> 00:05:33,292
<i>but they're Dallas Cowboy</i>
<i>cheerleaders.</i>

119
00:05:33,375 --> 00:05:34,833
<i>[horse neighs]</i>

120
00:05:34,917 --> 00:05:36,875
Pretty weird gifts
from San Diego,

121
00:05:36,958 --> 00:05:38,458
wouldn't you say?

122
00:05:38,542 --> 00:05:42,250
<i>A few weeks later, I snooped</i>
<i>on Grandma telling Mama</i>

123
00:05:42,333 --> 00:05:44,667
<i>that Papa was </i>muy misterioso.</i>

124
00:05:44,750 --> 00:05:48,500
A very strange response,
wouldn't you say?

125
00:05:48,583 --> 00:05:51,000
<i>So I decided to dig</i>
<i>a little deeper.</i>

126
00:05:51,083 --> 00:05:53,250
<i>I looked into his drawers,</i>
<i>and sure enough,</i>

127
00:05:53,333 --> 00:05:55,417
<i>I found his suit</i>
<i>and briefcase.</i>

128
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:57,042
- Dad doesn't own a briefcase.

129
00:05:57,125 --> 00:05:58,625
<i>You mean his tool kit?</i>

130
00:05:58,708 --> 00:06:00,667
<i>- I'm pretty sure</i>
<i>it was a briefcase.</i>

131
00:06:00,750 --> 00:06:01,667
- That's ridiculous.

132
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:03,292
When has Dad ever worked
an office job?

133
00:06:04,583 --> 00:06:05,542
- Sure.
Tool kit.

134
00:06:05,625 --> 00:06:06,542
Whatever.

135
00:06:06,625 --> 00:06:08,375
<i>Point is, it was missing.</i>

136
00:06:08,458 --> 00:06:10,417
Two important items
of business,

137
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:11,875
wouldn't you say?

138
00:06:11,958 --> 00:06:14,292
<i>At this point,</i>
<i>it all started to make sense.</i>

139
00:06:14,375 --> 00:06:15,500
<i>- What are you getting at?</i>

140
00:06:17,542 --> 00:06:20,500
<i>♪ ♪</i>

141
00:06:20,583 --> 00:06:21,792
- Just imagine it.

142
00:06:21,875 --> 00:06:23,708
<i>[exciting music]</i>

143
00:06:23,792 --> 00:06:25,625
<i>Always on the run,</i>

144
00:06:25,708 --> 00:06:27,500
<i>traveling to cool locations...</i>

145
00:06:27,583 --> 00:06:31,000
<i>♪ ♪</i>

146
00:06:31,083 --> 00:06:32,750
<i>Fighting henchmen.</i>

147
00:06:32,833 --> 00:06:39,750
<i>♪ ♪</i>

148
00:06:47,333 --> 00:06:50,417
<i>Knowing secrets</i>
<i>that could destroy lives.</i>

149
00:06:54,542 --> 00:06:56,458
- Wow.

150
00:06:56,542 --> 00:06:57,417
- I knew I had something.

151
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:59,000
- You, uh...

152
00:06:59,083 --> 00:07:00,125
you really got me there,
Marcela.

153
00:07:00,208 --> 00:07:03,500
I definitely thought you were
going somewhere with this.

154
00:07:03,583 --> 00:07:06,542
- But it's true.
It's just like the movies.

155
00:07:06,625 --> 00:07:08,083
Here, there's more proof.

156
00:07:08,167 --> 00:07:09,708
- I think I've seen enough.

157
00:07:09,792 --> 00:07:11,500
This just confirms
what I already know.

158
00:07:11,583 --> 00:07:13,458
- No, but listen.
It explains a lot.

159
00:07:13,542 --> 00:07:14,458
- This explains nothing.

160
00:07:14,542 --> 00:07:17,167
It...it's not real.

161
00:07:17,250 --> 00:07:20,292
- Him not calling anymore
or having time to write,

162
00:07:20,375 --> 00:07:21,792
he's trying to protect us.

163
00:07:21,875 --> 00:07:23,375
- If he was trying
to protect us,

164
00:07:23,458 --> 00:07:25,292
then he'd be here right now.

165
00:07:25,375 --> 00:07:27,458
- Stop saying "was."

166
00:07:27,542 --> 00:07:30,375
He's still here.
He's still trying.

167
00:07:30,458 --> 00:07:32,167
I don't understand
why you never missed him.

168
00:07:32,250 --> 00:07:33,958
- There was nothing
to miss, Marcela.

169
00:07:34,042 --> 00:07:35,750
He was never here for us
when he was here,

170
00:07:35,833 --> 00:07:37,750
and he was never there
for Mom either.

171
00:07:39,208 --> 00:07:41,917
- Where are you going?

172
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,042
[speaking Spanish]

173
00:07:43,125 --> 00:07:44,042
[grunts]

174
00:07:44,125 --> 00:07:45,208
- What's your damage?

175
00:07:45,292 --> 00:07:47,208
- If you think Papa's
as bad as you say he is,

176
00:07:47,292 --> 00:07:49,833
then you're not
too different from him.

177
00:07:49,917 --> 00:07:51,250
- Then look
at the letter, Rogelio.

178
00:07:51,333 --> 00:07:52,458
- Just shut up
and leave it alone!

179
00:07:52,542 --> 00:07:53,458
- I won't.

180
00:07:53,542 --> 00:07:54,500
Quit acting like a coward

181
00:07:54,583 --> 00:07:56,042
and admit
that you care about him.

182
00:07:56,125 --> 00:07:57,417
- He stole Mom's money.

183
00:07:57,500 --> 00:07:59,208
- What?

184
00:07:59,292 --> 00:08:00,542
- Do you want
to know the truth?

185
00:08:00,625 --> 00:08:01,667
Screw reading the letter.

186
00:08:01,750 --> 00:08:03,542
Do you want to know why
Dad stopped writing to us?

187
00:08:03,625 --> 00:08:04,625
Do you?

188
00:08:06,292 --> 00:08:07,667
Well, if you searched
hard enough,

189
00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:10,125
you would've realized
that Dad did take his tool kit

190
00:08:10,208 --> 00:08:11,500
<i>and his suit.</i>

191
00:08:11,583 --> 00:08:14,000
<i>He also took all the money</i>
<i>in Mom's savings bag</i>

192
00:08:14,083 --> 00:08:16,667
<i>and lied about paying it back</i>
<i>when he got to the States.</i>

193
00:08:16,750 --> 00:08:19,167
- What are you talking about?
He sent us money.

194
00:08:19,250 --> 00:08:20,667
- What, once or twice?

195
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:22,292
Everyone knows
that when you go to the U.S.,

196
00:08:22,375 --> 00:08:23,333
you don't come back.

197
00:08:23,417 --> 00:08:24,417
How don't you see it?

198
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:26,667
- That's not true.
- Everyone knows the truth.

199
00:08:28,292 --> 00:08:30,167
The whole neighborhood.
Everyone but you.

200
00:08:30,250 --> 00:08:32,583
- No, but Papa--
- Get it in your head!

201
00:08:32,667 --> 00:08:34,000
He's gone!

202
00:08:34,792 --> 00:08:35,750
[gunshot fires]

203
00:08:35,833 --> 00:08:36,958
<i>[somber music]</i>

204
00:08:37,042 --> 00:08:39,792
<i>He started a new life</i>
<i>with a new American woman...</i>

205
00:08:39,875 --> 00:08:42,417
<i>♪ ♪</i>

206
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:44,667
<i>Having the time of his life...</i>

207
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:47,333
<i>♪ ♪</i>

208
00:08:47,417 --> 00:08:48,708
- You're lying, Rogelio.

209
00:08:48,792 --> 00:08:51,208
<i>- Kissing good night</i>
<i>his new, blonde kids.</i>

210
00:08:51,292 --> 00:08:53,333
- Shut up!

211
00:08:53,417 --> 00:08:55,375
- He's a lazy coward,
and he forgot all about us.

212
00:08:55,458 --> 00:08:56,542
Grow up!

213
00:08:56,625 --> 00:08:57,917
- Stop it!

214
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:05,083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

215
00:09:35,042 --> 00:09:42,042
<i>♪ ♪</i>

216
00:09:47,083 --> 00:09:48,667
[paper ripping]

217
00:09:54,125 --> 00:09:59,917
<i>♪ ♪</i>

218
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,500
Leave me alone, Rogelio.
I don't want to see you.

219
00:10:02,583 --> 00:10:05,292
- Please, just listen to me.

220
00:10:08,167 --> 00:10:10,167
I didn't mean to act
like such a...

221
00:10:13,708 --> 00:10:15,333
I'm sorry, Marcela.

222
00:10:15,417 --> 00:10:18,125
- That's because you are.

223
00:10:18,208 --> 00:10:20,958
Did you just come back here
to tell me more about Dad

224
00:10:21,042 --> 00:10:22,958
having fun
with his white family?

225
00:10:23,042 --> 00:10:24,208
- That's not true.

226
00:10:25,333 --> 00:10:26,917
- What?

227
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:29,542
- I read the letter.

228
00:10:29,625 --> 00:10:31,208
I was wrong.

229
00:10:31,292 --> 00:10:32,875
- What did it say?

230
00:10:32,958 --> 00:10:35,750
- Remember how you said
Dad may be traveling?

231
00:10:35,833 --> 00:10:38,625
Turns out
you were pretty close.

232
00:10:38,708 --> 00:10:40,500
Dad's been traveling
from town to town,

233
00:10:40,583 --> 00:10:42,917
trying to find better-paying
jobs along the way.

234
00:10:44,292 --> 00:10:46,083
Seems really happy
getting to experience

235
00:10:46,167 --> 00:10:48,042
and explore the U.S.

236
00:10:49,375 --> 00:10:50,625
- But?

237
00:10:52,458 --> 00:10:55,917
- But, sometimes,

238
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,542
when you have something
so good, it...

239
00:10:58,625 --> 00:11:01,500
can be hard to let go of.

240
00:11:01,583 --> 00:11:03,417
Sometimes, that decision
can turn your whole life

241
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:06,000
upside down.

242
00:11:06,083 --> 00:11:08,375
Dad made a dumb decision.

243
00:11:10,250 --> 00:11:12,208
He was letting us know
that this was gonna be

244
00:11:12,292 --> 00:11:13,667
the last letter
we'll ever receive.

245
00:11:15,708 --> 00:11:17,208
It was his good-bye.

246
00:11:20,708 --> 00:11:22,583
- I don't believe you.

247
00:11:22,667 --> 00:11:24,083
I-I don't--
it probably meant

248
00:11:24,167 --> 00:11:25,917
he's coming home
and can't write at the moment.

249
00:11:27,625 --> 00:11:29,667
- I'm so sorry, Marcela.

250
00:11:31,625 --> 00:11:34,542
<i>[somber music]</i>

251
00:11:34,625 --> 00:11:41,583
<i>♪ ♪</i>

252
00:12:11,458 --> 00:12:13,750
We're gonna be okay.

253
00:12:17,958 --> 00:12:19,583
- [sniffles]

254
00:12:24,542 --> 00:12:26,125
How do you know?

255
00:12:27,250 --> 00:12:28,875
- Well, you got me.

256
00:12:32,292 --> 00:12:35,500
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

257
00:12:35,583 --> 00:12:41,667
